he experiences of patients and staff, and the vital grassroots activism that pressed the federal government to acknowledge its treaty obligations.A disturbing look at the dark side of the liberal welfare state, Separate Beds reveals a history of racism and negligence in health care for Canada’s First Nations that should never be forgotten.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aDiscrimination in medical carezCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aIndians of North AmericaxHospital carezCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aIndians, Treatment ofzCanada. 0aMedical policyzCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 7aMEDICAL / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066595640uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144266311440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442663114423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442663114.jpg  a978-3-11-066595-6  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles